#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga "
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 21. Paṭhamakoṭigāmasutta → vijjā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Paṭhamakoṭigāmasutta "
msgstr "21. At the Village of Koṭi (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn56.21:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati koṭigāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis at the village of Koṭi. "

msgctxt "sn56.21:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "sn56.21:1.3"
msgid "“catunnaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasaccānaṃ ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, not understanding and not penetrating four noble truths, both you and I have wandered and transmigrated for such a very long time. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.432, sc2
msgctxt "sn56.21:2.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.2"
msgid "Dukkhassa, bhikkhave, ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. "
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, "

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.3"
msgid "Dukkhasamudayassa ariyasaccassa … pe … "
msgstr "the origin of suffering, "

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.4"
msgid "dukkhanirodhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … "
msgstr "the cessation of suffering, "

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.5"
msgid "dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. "
msgstr "and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.6"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhanirodhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ; ucchinnā bhavataṇhā, khīṇā bhavanetti; natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. "
msgstr "These noble truths of suffering, origin, cessation, and the path have been understood and comprehended. Craving for continued existence has been cut off; the attachment to continued existence is ended; now there are no more future lives.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.21:3.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn56.21:3.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.1"
msgid "“Catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ, "
msgstr "“Because of not truly seeing "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.2"
msgid "Yathābhūtaṃ adassanā; "
msgstr "the four noble truths, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Saṃsitaṃ → saṃsaraṃ (bj) | saṃsaritaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.3"
msgid "Saṃsitaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ, "
msgstr "we have transmigrated for a long time "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.4"
msgid "Tāsu tāsveva jātisu. "
msgstr "from one rebirth to the next. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#. VAR: Tāni → yāni (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.1"
msgid "Tāni etāni diṭṭhāni, "
msgstr "But now that these truths have been seen, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.2"
msgid "bhavanetti samūhatā; "
msgstr "the attachment to rebirth is eradicated. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.3"
msgid "Ucchinnaṃ mūlaṃ dukkhassa, "
msgstr "The root of suffering is cut off, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.4"
msgid "natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. "
msgstr "now there are no more future lives.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
